The draw for the semi-final of this season’s FA Cup will be conducted on Sunday night. The draw will take place during the half-time interval of the match between Newcastle United and Manchester City, which kicks off at 18:30 BST. Man United will battle Norwich City on Saturday evening for a place in the last four. The tie will be decided on the night with no replays. Should Man United beat Norwich, they will be ball no.3. The numbers for the full draw, containing all Premier League clubs, are as follows: Norwich City or Manchester United
Sheffield United or Arsenal
Leicester City or Chelsea
Newcastle or Manchester City The draw will be broadcast on BBC One within the UK, the Emirates FA Cup’s official Facebook, Twitter and YouTube accounts. The semi-finals of the Emirates FA Cup are due to take place over the weekend of July 18 and 19, with the final scheduled for August 1.